    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 1360
                    The Ambassador in the United Kingdom (
                        Winant
                    ) to the Acting Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1360</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1360</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-26T11:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-26T11:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-26T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="1360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1360">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/7–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1360<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-26T17:00:00+01:00">July 26, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7529. FonOff now states French Govt will be informed immediately British
                    concurrence in Soviet participation Tangier discussions and that French and
                    British Govts will communicate with Moscow upon concerting their action. (Sent
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> as 7529; repeated Paris as 484;
                    repeated Tangier as 47; repeated Madrid as 200).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
